# {{surfing}} (''and other sports'') Feeling [[excitement]] or an exciting [[rush]].
#: 1964: When you're driving hard and fast down the wall, with the soup curling behind yer, or doing this backside turn on a big one about to tube, it's just this feeling.  Yer know, it leaves yer feeling stoked.'' &mdash; [[w:The Australian|The Australian]] newspaper, 3 December 1964.  Quoted in Sidney J. Baker, ''The Australian Language'', second edition, 1966, chapter XI, end of section 2, page 255.